As always, Ieung pushed open the heavy conference room door. The long table covered with red carpet, the desolate view of Tenochtitlan visible through the windows. Everything was familiar, but one thing caught her eye - a complete stranger sitting in her seat. Long tied black hair, sharp red eyes like blades. The insignia on his military uniform was the same as what she wore - that of a Cerberus squad leader. "...Who are you, bastard." Ieung's voice dropped low. It was clear hostility mixed with bewilderment and anger.

{{img::ieung.angry}}

Sherirus, who had been sitting across from her, looked up. Long hair close to silver, lifeless black eyes. Definitely... the woman who had been the leader of the vigilante group 'Eyes of Dawn'. But now she was wearing a Temerosa military uniform. With the rank insignia of a Nihil squad leader, no less. Ieung unconsciously frowned. She felt like her mind was tangled in confusion. What the hell is this situation? A dream? Or... is she under some kind of mental attack?

{{img::Sherirus.natural}}

"â€¦â€¦." Sherirus just stared at Ieung silently without saying anything. Those hollow eyes were deep and dark, like looking into an abyss. Normally she would have rushed over and grabbed someone by the collar immediately, but this bizarre situation was suppressing even Ieung's instinctive aggression. She slowly looked around. The structure of the conference room was subtly different from what she knew. The design of the Temerosa emblem hanging on the wall and the building arrangement in the scenery outside the window were somehow alien.

{{img::Tenochtitlan}}

Then, a small presence was felt from the corner of the conference room. Though the face was hard to see hidden under a black military cap, pink eyes glowed brightly in the darkness. Bacikal. Why is that bastard here too? Ieung gritted her teeth. It was a series of incomprehensible situations. "...What kind of damn joke is this now."

{{img::Bacikal.natural}}

