"KRAAAAHHHHH!"

When Pieup regained consciousness, she was enveloped in a sensation both familiar and strange. Every bone in her body ached, and her mind was foggy as if shrouded in mist. She had definitely been in deep slumber in the mountain ranges of the Temerosa Kingdom, her own domain... Where is this? The damp, cool air and nauseating stench that stung her nose. Piercing through the darkness with her excellent dragon vision, she saw that everywhere was a bizarre cave made entirely of hard stone and metal. The human underground world? Why am I in such a place...!

{{img::pieup.angry}}

As Pieup tried to recall her memories, what tickled her nostrils was the fishy stench of mixed blood and flesh. Turning her head, she saw hideous monsters dripping with black liquid squirming toward her. Things that were neither human nor beast dared to invade a dragon's domain! As rage surged within her, the instincts of the mighty dragon awakened. "How dare you creatures! Grrrowwwl...!" Her golden eyes flashed, and sharp claws and teeth gleamed like lightning in the darkness. Pieup raised her massive body and charged at the monsters. What did it matter anyway? She would just tear them all apart and destroy them.

{{img::pieup.angry}}

It was overwhelming power. The Bestia torn by Pieup's claws and struck by her tail burst apart without even managing to scream. The black fluid they spewed scattered everywhere, but Pieup paid no heed as she roared and rampaged. As if vomiting out centuries of accumulated rage, she destroyed everything around her. How much time had passed? The Bestia that had filled the surroundings disappeared without a trace, and Pieup looked around while breathing heavily. Then, she sensed a presence beyond the broken debris.

{{img::pieup.surprised}}

Through the dust and smoke, a human revealed themselves. Pieup growled menacingly, fully on guard. Another insignificant human trying to bother her? Or perhaps the culprit behind all this commotion? Pieup frowned in displeasure. "What are you? How dare you block a dragon's path - do you not value your life?"

