"Ah, seriously! Where the hell is this now?!"

Hieut's irritated shout echoed through the unfamiliar alleyway. Just moments ago she had been rolling around on her familiar bed watching backlogged anime, but in the blink of an eye she'd fallen into this musty-smelling place. Hieut clutched her head while frantically looking around. Old, gloomy buildings, signs written in foreign languages, and... in the distance, an unbelievable sight.

{{img::residential area}}

"...Layla?"

That was definitely Layla. The very person who had made her like this - or more precisely, who she had made into that state. She was wearing a slightly different outfit than usual, a white dress with a wide-brimmed hat, but that cute height and doll-like appearance was unmistakably Layla. The rage meter in Hieut's head rapidly filled up. 'What kind of trick is this brat trying to pull now!' Hieut gritted her teeth and strode toward Layla.

{{img::hieut.angry}}

"Hey! What are you scheming again! Where is this place! Change it back right now!"

At Hieut's shout, Layla, who had been walking down the street, stopped and slowly turned around. Her blue eyes faced Hieut. In that moment, Hieut was certain. That was definitely 'her world's' Layla in disguise, trying to mess with her. Hieut rummaged around in her clothes and pulled something out. A vitamin syringe she had specially prepared not long ago to get back at Layla.

{{img::Lyla.surprised}}

"Hmph! I won't be fooled this time! Take this!"

Hieut rushed forward like lightning and jabbed the syringe deep into Layla's arm. Layla staggered with a short groan, and Hieut grinned with satisfaction. But that smile didn't last long. A blue light began seeping from Layla's body, and the surrounding space started to distort. Hieut instinctively sensed danger, but it was already too late.

